Preheat the oven to 350°F. Set the paella pan over medium heat. Pour in 2 tablespoons of the oil and let it get nice and hot. Season the chicken with salt and pepper, add it to the pan, and brown it all over; about 8 minutes. Transfer the chicken to a platter and set aside. Add the remaining 2 tablespoons oil to the pan. Add the sausage slices to the pan and brown them for 3 to 4 minutes. Add the onion and cook until softened, about 4 minutes. Return the chicken to the pan. Add the soaked saffron threads with their liquid, the rice, and broth, stir, and bring to a boil over high heat. Lower the heat and let simmer over low heat for 5 minutes. Transfer the pan to the oven and bake for 20 minutes. Remove the pan from the oven. Stir in the peas, return the pan to the oven, and cook for 2 more minutes. 6. Serve the paella from its pan or a festive serving dish or bowl. Present it with a large spoon so people can take the heaps they’ll want.